  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required gradation levels. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved 1 vs. required 2) is judged tolerable given medium model risk level, corroborating multi-team blind analysis results, and the conservative nature of the single-condition ASTM F1717 protocol. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-specified E/uval < 1.96 acceptance criterion. Comprehensive Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification across all model inputs confirms that prediction intervals encompass experimental observations. The credibility evidence is sufficient to support regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
